Place @brown rice{3/4%cup} and a large pinch of @salt{} in a medium #pot{} with
enough water to cover by 3 inches. Bring to a boil. Cook until tender, about
~{25%minutes}, then drain. Return to pot and keep covered off heat until meal
is ready.

Wash and dry all produce. Core, seed, and remove white ribs from @yellow bell
pepper{1}(cored, seeded, and sliced thinly crosswise). Slice thinly
crosswise. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and
sliced thinly). Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced).
Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}(peeled and minced). Mince or grate
@garlic{2%cloves}(minced or grated). Trim any tough ends from
@sugar snap peas{6%ounce}(trimmed). Cut @lime{1}(cut into wedges).

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in large pan over
medium-high heat. Add onion, garlic, scallions, and ginger. Cook, tossing,
until just barely softened, about ~{2-3%minutes}.

Toss bell pepper into pan. Cook until just starting to turn tender, another
~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss snap peas into pan. Cook until just starting to turn tender,
~{2-3%minutes}. Add 3 TBSP @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp} and a squeeze of lime juice.
Continue tossing until sauce is mixed in and heated through, about
~{1%minute}.

Divide rice between plates, then top with stir-fry. Serve with lime wedges on
the side for squeezing.